data.description: This 3 bedroom and 2 bath colonial set on a landscaped corner homesite in Roland Terrace offers a design aesthetic of a traditional 1,400 sq ft home. The classic interiors of this home  offers tons of natural light and boast a large family room with wood burning stove and a walkout to a sizeable privacy fenced yard with 2 gated entries, a concrete patio, a floating deck, and a garden shed. Next to the living room is the eat-in kitchen highlighted by Corian® counters, complementing tile backsplash, raised frame wood cabinetry, classic white appliances, great table space, and just a step up to the laundry room.  From Church Street,  you enter through a wide foyer to the upper level including the bedrooms, a full bath, and stairs to the core living areas.   Enjoy this Anne Arundel County location close to shopping, dining, Curtis Bay, the Patapsco River, and easy access commuter routes.
